rComments: One of the best profs I've had at U of T. Showing up and participating will give you a big advantage. His assignments are clearly laid out from the beginning. Don't neglect to think them through early on - creativity and thorough thought are important, and good spelling and grammar will take you far. Great for fans of Marshall McLuhan.

This course is very entertaining: readings are simple and light and there are movie screenings. The downsides of this course are assignments that are barely reflective of and are remotely related to the course content. Pungente is an approachable, understanding, and helpful instructor. He is very keen on grammar, so make sure your writing is good.
